 :tx/rationale "AUDIT-COH-4: Three parallel F(S) computation paths produce different values for identical store state. (1) Batch path (bilateral.rs:869 compute_fitness): rescans store datoms, uses full methodology M(t) score. (2) Views path (store.rs:770-890 views.fitness()): uses incremental accumulators, different H (harvest quality) heuristic based on observation density. (3) Policy path (bilateral.rs:729 compute_fitness_from_policy): reads policy boundary weights, maps boundaries to 7-component struct by positional index (fragile). Store::fitness() at store.rs:1650 tries policy path first, falls back to views. The policy path has one SpecImplBoundary registered by default; boundaries[1..6] get vacuous 1.0 scores, producing inflated totals. SOLUTION: Unify into a single canonical path. Use MaterializedViews accumulators as the single computation source (they are maintained incrementally and are always current). Eliminate the batch rescan path. The policy path should read FROM views, not scan independently. VERIFICATION: After unification, compute F(S) via the single path; compare to both old paths on a test store, verify the canonical path agrees with batch (the most correct one). DEPENDENCIES: Interacts with AUDIT-SOUND-2 (F(S) monotonicity) and AUDIT-PERF-1 (scan elimination). Unifying paths eliminates both the disagreement and the performance overhead."
